						               													<description>Full name of the game is: Sesam Grammatikkspill - Ali Baba &amp;aring;pner d&amp;oslash;ren til hulen (&amp;quot;Sesam Grammar Game - Ali Baba opens up the cave door&amp;quot;). This is a flexible ruled grammar (educational) quiz game.&amp;#10;There are 56 assignments. In the first 28 assignments (each containing 21-28 words/word spaces) your task is to categorize words in their correct word classes. The last 28 assignments (each containing 2-10 sentences) you need to define each word's correct grammar name in the sentence. The answer is given by taking tokens, like for instance &amp;quot;conjuction&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;preposition&amp;quot; (black) or &amp;quot;object&amp;quot; and predicate&amp;quot; (red) and put them on the word space. For each correct answer you gain 2 points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The idea of the game is teaching and testing grammar skills, and was encouraged for use in schools.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents:&amp;#10;14 cardboard boards with 56 assignments&amp;#10;Cardboard word class tokens&amp;#10;Box inserts for word class tokens&amp;#10;1 booklet with rules and answers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
